If `if (def_ret == -2) dgst = NULL; else` is inserted before [this line](https://github.com/openssl/openssl/blob/d0a3b9d1eb1fc510ec3447b44803bbf5520a0c47/apps/ca.c#L810), the verification succeeds. 

Explanation: The [documentation ](https://www.openssl.org/docs/man3.1/man3/EVP_PKEY_get_default_digest_name.html) for `EVP_PKEY_get_default_digest_name` (used in the preceding line) states: "In particular a return value of -2 indicates the operation is not supported by the public key algorithm." If getting a default digest name is not supported, it should be OK that the `dgst` value is set to `NULL`. With that, the `dgst` value in the later [call](https://github.com/openssl/openssl/blob/d0a3b9d1eb1fc510ec3447b44803bbf5520a0c47/apps/ca.c#L1929) to `do_X509_sign` is still 'NULL'.

@baentsch Any opinion on that?
